-<br/>
“There’s one character, in the world of characters, that I like the most, and that character is the colon.” Tal R uses the colon to illustrate the relationship between the past, present and future. In this film, Tal R – on the brink of turning fifty – looks forwards as well as backwards and shares what being an artist and a human being means to him, and why the two can’t be separated.<br/>
-<br/>
LL’Editions Cinema includes a stream of new and old videos that inspire us. We’ve collected artist’s talks, studio visits, documentaries and interviews with artists, architects and designers and have over 200 videos.<br/>
